│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformation is performed by `instcombine`. The goal is to canonicalize `select (icmp ne x, 0), (cttz x), C` to `select (icmp eq x, 0), C, (cttz x)` and then potentially sink the │
│ `cttz` into the `else` branch. As part of this, it seems to be changing `is_zero_poison` to `true`, assuming the `cttz` is only executed when `x` is non-zero. However, it fails to      │
