│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Let's analyze the failing test from the log:                                                                                                                                             │
│ `FAIL: LLVM :: Transforms/InstCombine/select-cmp-cttz-ctlz.ll`                                                                                                                           │
│ The test expects `i1 true` but gets `i1 false`. This means my change is too restrictive.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The original reproducer was:                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```llvm                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ define i32 @test_cttz_not_bw_noundef(i32 %x) {                                                                                                                                           │
│   %ct = tail call noundef i32 @llvm.cttz.i32(i32 %x, i1 false)                                                                                                                           │
│   %cmp = icmp ne i32 %x, 0                                                                                                                                                               │
│   %res = select i1 %cmp, i32 %ct, i32 123                                                                                                                                                │
│   ret i32 %res                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ The key here is that the "else" value of the select is `123`.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The logic I modified is in `InstCombineSelect.cpp` around line 1227:                                                                                                                     │
│ ```c++                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   // The ValueOnZero is not the bitwidth. But if the cttz/ctlz (and optional                                                                                                             │
│   // zext/trunc) have one use (ending at the select), the cttz/ctlz result will                                                                                                          │
│   // not be used if the input is zero. Relax to 'zero is poison' for that case.                                                                                                          │
│   if (II->hasOneUse() && SelectArg->hasOneUse() &&                                                                                                                                       │
│       !match(II->getArgOperand(1), m_One()))                                                                                                                                             │
│     II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::getTrue(II->getContext()));                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This logic is triggered when the "else" value is *not* the bitwidth.                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The logic just before it is:                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```c++                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   // Check if the value propagated on zero is a constant number equal to the                                                                                                             │
│   // sizeof in bits of 'Count'.                                                                                                                                                          │
│   unsigned SizeOfInBits = Count->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();                                                                                                                       │
│   if (match(ValueOnZero, m_SpecificInt(SizeOfInBits))) {                                                                                                                                 │
│     // Explicitly clear the 'is_zero_poison' flag. It's always valid to go from                                                                                                          │
│     // true to false on this flag, so we can replace it for all users.                                                                                                                   │
│     II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::getFalse(II->getContext()));                                                                                                                       │
│     // ...                                                                                                                                                                               │
│     return SelectArg;                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This handles the case where the "else" value *is* the bitwidth. In this case, it transforms `cttz(x, true)` to `cttz(x, false)`.                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My change prevents the `false` -> `true` transformation for `noundef` calls. It seems there is a test case that relies on this. The transformation is valid if the `cttz` call is truly  │
